---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Internal Penetration Testing | Sheepdog Cyber Defense" description="Internal penetration testing for Texas businesses. Assess what happens after an attacker gains network access." showMatrix={true}>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "name": "Internal Penetration Testing",
    "description": "Assessment of internal network security, privilege escalation, lateral movement, and Active Directory security.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Sheepdog Cyber Defense",
      "url": "https://sheepdogcyberdefense.com"
    },
    "areaServed": {
      "@type": "State",
      "name": "Texas"
    },
    "serviceType": "Penetration Testing",
    "url": "https://sheepdogcyberdefense.com/services/internal-penetration-testing"
  }
  </script>
  <section>
    <h1>Internal Penetration Testing</h1>
    <p class="lead">We test what happens after an attacker gets inside your network. This is about understanding your exposure from within.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What It Covers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Internal network architecture review</li>
      <li>Workstation and server assessment</li>
      <li>Privilege escalation paths</li>
      <li>Lateral movement possibilities</li>
      <li>Active Directory security</li>
      <li>Credential harvesting risks</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Our Approach</h2>
    <p>We simulate an attacker who has gained initial access—either through a phished credential, a compromised endpoint, or physical access. From there, we see how far we can go and what we can access.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Deliverables</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Findings report with proof of access</li>
      <li>Network architecture recommendations</li>
      <li>Remediation roadmap</li>
      <li>Executive summary</li>
      <li>Debrief call</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Typical Timeline</h2>
    <p>Internal tests typically take 2-3 weeks depending on network size and complexity.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What You'll Need</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Scope definition (network ranges)</li>
      <li>Test account (domain user)</li>
      <li>Network documentation</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Request a Quote</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead { font-size: 1.25rem; max-width: 700px; }
  section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .cta { padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
</style>
